    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It's not just about \"complex factors,\" it's about the real-world output which is inequity. A lottery avoids these biased patterns entirely. If the council switches to a lottery tomorrow, the demographic disparities we're seeing will disappear because the system won't be \"optimizing\" based on these controversial socioeconomic metrics. Why shouldn't we just move to the lottery system now to stop the harm?",
